This dataset contains whole brain task and resting-state fMRI data for 96 subjects during a single recording session. Subjects performed the Concrete Permuted Rule Operations task (C-PRO).

For a description of the task and data methods, please view the methods and task description in:

Ito, T., Kulkarni, K.R., Schultz, D.H., Mill, R.D., Chen, R.H., Solomyak, L.I., Cole, M.W., 2017. Cognitive task information is transferred between brain regions via resting-state network topology. Nature Communications. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-017-01000-w

Please also cite the above reference if you use these data.

Some other studies that used this dataset:

Schultz, Douglas H., Takuya Ito, Levi I. Solomyak, Richard H. Chen, Ravi D. Mill, Alan Anticevic, and Michael W. Cole. (2019). “Global Connectivity of the Fronto-Parietal Cognitive Control Network Is Related to Depression Symptoms in the General Population.” Network Neuroscience 3 (1): 107–23. doi:10.1162/netn_a_00056.

Cocuzza, Carrisa V., Takuya Ito, Douglas Schultz, Danielle S. Bassett, and Michael W. Cole. (2020). “Flexible Coordinator and Switcher Hubs for Adaptive Task Control.” The Journal of Neuroscience 40 (36): 6949–68. doi:10.1523/JNEUROSCI.2559-19.2020.

For any questions, please send inquiries to taku.ito1@gmail.com
